Current stabilize training now appears fundamentally healthy.

The aircraft:
- flies stably
- avoids stalls
- maintains airspeed
- uses moderate controls
- visually behaves realistically

The remaining issue is:
occasional crash episodes (~11%).

This is now a robustness/generalization problem,
not a basic flight-stability problem.

